Enhancements and changes made in this release include:

  - Enhanced version of C/MS Utilities Disk
        
    Programs  such as APLAY.EXE, PACK.EXE and UNPACK.EXE  have  been 
    upgraded to support monochrome graphic. Refer to the README file  
    in the Utilities Disk for more details.

    A  new utility, CAPTURE.COM is now included in this package  for 
    you to capture CGA or MGA graphic in C/MS format. Graphics  that 
    are  captured  can   be used in C/MS graphic  programs  such  as 
    APLAY.


  - CMSDRV.COM version 3.10

    This  version of CMSDRV can be uninstalled from the system.  You 
    can   enter  the following command to remove CMSDRV  which   has     
    been installed in your system:

          CMSDRV /U

    If  your  system is installed with earlier versions  of  CMSDRV, 
    this  switch   will   not  work.  It will  only  uninstall   the  
    installed CMSDRV which is version 3.10 or later. 

    Ensure  that  you  replace all CMSDRV.COM  you  have  with  this 
    version.


  - PLAYER.EXE version 3.11

    This version of PLAYER is updated to work with the new version 
    of CMSDRV.


  - INSTALL.EXE version 3.10

    This  version  of INSTALL program has been  simplified.
    Refer to next section for more details.



